Compare REDCap Data Columns to Data Dictionary

compare_cols_to_dict.Rd

This function compares the column names of a dataset against the variable names specified in a REDCap data dictionary. It reports discrepancies and adds any missing dictionary variables to the dataset as NA columns.

Usage

compare_cols_to_dict(dayta, dictPath)

Arguments

dayta

A data frame or tibble representing your dataset (e.g., from REDCap export).

dictPath

A string. Path to the REDCap data dictionary in CSV format.

Value

A data frame with all columns defined in the dictionary. Any missing columns originally absent from the dataset will be added and filled with NA.

Details

Useful for ensuring consistency between your dataset and a REDCap project structure, especially before importing data or validating fields.

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
updated_data <- compare_cols_to_dict(my_data, "REDCap_DataDictionary.csv")
} # }
